  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to evaluate the utility of fibrinolysis when draining an
      abdominal abscess as defined by length of stay after drainage.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis is that fibrinolysis of a abscess will shorten hospital stay compared to
      drainage alone.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
